    "This involved applying max-pooling in the normals stream and attention pooling in the coordinate stream.",
    "However, various training experiments with the described setup using the Teeth3DS data set showed that separating the streams has no positive influence.",
    "Consequently, in pursuit of a simpler variant, we abandoned the notion of separating normals and coordinates into separate streams.",
    "Instead, we opted for a unified stream employing the edge convolution operation specified in Eq. 3 followed by max-pooling.",
